Ukraine’s deputy defence minister said on Tuesday evening that Kyiv’s forces were still holding out in the eastern salt mining town of Soledar despite a massive Russian onslaught, “There isn’t one house left intact. Apartments were burning, breaking in half.”  — Olha, 60, speaking in an evacuee centre in Kramatorsk. She said she had fled Soledar after moving from apartment to apartment as each was destroyed in tank battles. (Compiled by Michael Perry, Raju Gopalakrishnan, Angus MacSwan and Mark Heinrich)